               <head>Kotah, history</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008116669 http://lccn.loc.gov/n84105083" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4061-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Copied from original leaves lacking a title or author</p>
                        <p>Excerpt from a larger, unidentified history on the <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7682" role="subject">Hādā</persName> (Hara) <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Rājpūt</term> state of <name type="place">Kotah</name> (formerly part of <name type="place">Bundi State</name>)
                        </p>
                        <p>Extending from the death of the state's founder, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7733" role="subject">Rāʾū Mādav Singh Hādā</persName> (Rao Madho Singh Hara) to the reign of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7693" role="subject">Mahārāʾū Bhīm Singh I</persName>(r. 1707-20)
                        </p>
                     </note>
